<L>__{exterior victoria monument street night (dusk)}
<A>__{calcutta broiling: buses, vendors, carts, rickshaws, children beg at car windows. the pals stand, uncertain, and for the first time a rickshaw fills hasari's eye, carrying two passengers. but now he shoulders his burden and leads the family toward the river. we hold until they grow small against the setting sun, gleaming red against the white domes of the victoria monument.}
